    <h2>Why IT Failures Are Particularly Costly for Real Estate Agencies</h2>

    <p>A real estate agency is a data-driven business running on tight legal deadlines. Trust accounting errors carry regulatory consequences under the Real Estate and Business Agents Act. Missed inspection records create liability. Unsigned lease documents delay occupancy and cost landlord clients rental income. Every hour of IT downtime in a real estate office translates into a measurable financial and reputational cost that cannot simply be recovered by working longer the next day.</p>

    <p>Real estate agencies also carry significant compliance obligations under the Australian Privacy Act with respect to the personal and financial information they hold for tenants, landlords and buyers. A security breach affecting client data is not just a reputational problem. It is a regulatory one. Agencies that do not have properly managed antivirus, device security and backup arrangements in place are exposed to risks that a single ransomware incident could make very real.</p>

    <p>Staff turnover in real estate is higher than most industries. New property managers and sales staff join regularly, each needing a correctly configured device with access to the right software, cloud accounts and internal systems from day one. Without a structured IT arrangement, each new starter costs hours of setup time that falls on whoever in the office is most technically capable, which is rarely the most productive use of their time.</p>

    <h2>The Most Common IT Problems We See in Perth Real Estate Agencies</h2>

    <p>After working with real estate businesses across Perth and the southern suburbs, the same IT problems appear repeatedly. Understanding them is the first step toward making sure they stop affecting your agency.</p>

    <ul class="problem-list">
      <li class="problem-item">
        <div class="problem-label">
          <span class="problem-icon">!</span>
          <span class="problem-label-text">Property management software going down</span>
        </div>
        <div class="problem-desc">PropertyMe, Console Cloud and PropertyTree outages are often caused by Windows update conflicts or network misconfigurations that were never properly addressed during initial setup. The software gets blamed when the underlying IT environment is the real cause.</div>
      </li>
      <li class="problem-item">
        <div class="problem-label">
          <span class="problem-icon">!</span>
          <span class="problem-label-text">Trust accounting software errors</span>
        </div>
        <div class="problem-desc">Rockend, REST Professional and Console trust accounting tools require consistent environments across all devices. Driver conflicts, outdated software versions and incorrect user permissions generate accounting errors that take hours to trace and correct at end of month.</div>
      </li>
      <li class="problem-item">
        <div class="problem-label">
          <span class="problem-icon">!</span>
          <span class="problem-label-text">DocuSign and digital signing failures</span>
        </div>
        <div class="problem-desc">Digital lease and contract signing through DocuSign and REI Forms Live fails when browser extensions conflict, security certificates expire or network settings block the required connections. This holds up lease signings and settlement completions at the worst possible moments.</div>
      </li>
      <li class="problem-item">
        <div class="problem-label">
          <span class="problem-icon">!</span>
          <span class="problem-label-text">Cloud file access problems in the field</span>
        </div>
        <div class="problem-desc">Property managers accessing inspection reports, tenancy agreements and condition reports from tablets or phones in the field encounter access problems when OneDrive or SharePoint synchronisation settings were never correctly configured across all devices.</div>
      </li>
      <li class="problem-item">
        <div class="problem-label">
          <span class="problem-icon">!</span>
          <span class="problem-label-text">Slow office computers affecting productivity</span>
        </div>
        <div class="problem-desc">Aging or poorly maintained computers slow down quoting, database searches and document processing across the office. The time lost each week across an entire team is rarely measured but consistently costs more than the IT support that would prevent it.</div>
      </li>
      <li class="problem-item">
        <div class="problem-label">
          <span class="problem-icon">!</span>
          <span class="problem-label-text">No secure backup of critical records</span>
        </div>
        <div class="problem-desc">Tenancy files, inspection records, maintenance history, landlord communications and financial records stored only on local drives or desktop folders are unprotected. A single hardware failure, theft or ransomware attack can permanently destroy records that carry legal obligations to retain.</div>
      </li>
    </ul>

    <p>Every one of these problems is preventable with the right IT support in place. None of them should be absorbing your team's time during a working day.</p>

